About Us

CryptoLeaf was founded after years of working in management and the investment industry. Too many innovative and visionary solutions to world environmental problems, go unnoticed in the traditional financing world based primarily on institutional investors.

Using cryptocurrency and smart contract technology, we want to help businesses and entrepreneurs turn their own ideas and visions into successful organisations. We want to help fund and guide businesses to their success. By creating our own cryptocurrency, we provide everyone on the planet the opportunity to support and fund environmental companies, initiatives and projects.

We become invested with each of the businesses we work with right from the very start. We support, guide and provide continuous business feedback to all our member companies.

Check out some of the great companies, which have already undergone our due diligence process and are ready to take things to the next level!

Using organic waste, they build self-sustainable bio-gas plants, producing electricity, heat, bio-gas and high quality fertiliser, all in one! At the same time, they remove organic waste from cities and farms, put it to good use and produce clean, free energy for whole communities and businesses.

Located in Eastern Europe with a size of up to 10,000 hectares (that’s 10km*10km!), this large scale Swiss Made agricultural business will be operating some of the most advanced German farming equipment, providing work for over 1500 seasonal employees and ensuring food production for the region. Future goals are to include autonomous driving farming machines, as well as setting up a bio-gas plant next door to make good use of organic and vegetable waste.

Cryptocurrency and Eco-Projects: Why?

Cryptocurrency and Eco-Projects: Why?

We asked ourselves the same question in the beginning of this journey. Why are we linking cryptocurrency with real-life ecological projects? Do we really need digital finance to make our mission a success?

Turns out you do! Funding projects using cryptocurrency gives control back to our contributors! Here’s why and what you can get out of it:

Distinctive features

Frictionless Funding

Tokenised crowdfunding – lower fees and more return to you

Milestone-based Funding

If projects fail to reach agreed upon milestones, the unused funds are returned to contributors.

Flexibility & Control

Reap the benefits of revenue sharing and be in control of where your contributions go, at all times.

Impact

Use cryptocurrency to affect real environmental changes in the world

Due Diligence

We fact-check all listed projects, no exceptions. You have the final vote.

Direct Democracy

Have a say in which projects receive funding and benefit from the success of those projects.

Direct democracy at work!

How does CryptoLeaf work?

1st Step Due Diligence

Before projects are listed, they undergo an extensive due diligence process, conducted by three independent experts on our team. If the project is deemed feasible, it is listed on our website. New projects are assessed based on several criteria.

2nd Step Listing and Funding

Once a project has been assessed, and listed on our website, and the community has voted, it can begin to receive funding. All projects are funded with Ethereum (ETH) . As easy as that . CryptoLeaf token holders will be able to use their LEAF tokens (CLF) to offset the usual transaction fee of up to 2.5% to only 0.1%.

3rd Step Milestone based Funding

One of the most risky developments in the cryptocurrency space has been the lack of contributor consideration when it comes to collecting funds for companies through token sales. Usually, once a token sale is completed successfully (companies reach their soft-cap) companies usually receive all the funds at once. Receiving all funds upfront also increases the risk of the founders of a particular project to run off with the collected sums, never to be heard of again. At CryptoLeaf we have implemented milestone based funding. That means more control to you, and less risk.

4th Step Revenue Sharing

Why do we require the payout to our contributors to be linked to the project's revenues instead of profts? It's quite simple: During the initial stage of any new project, net profits are usually quite low, because companies in such cases usually reinvest their profits back into the project itself. Hence, they deduct their reinvestment as an expense. This can make sense in certain instances, such as if that company is a start-up or is pursuing an expansion of operations. However, it could also mean that our contributors receive very little back from the projects they help fund.

5th Step Token Payout

Revenue sharing is paid out over time, and in the form of ETH. Every time a listed company project shares its revenues with our contributors, contributors receive 80 % of each payout , while cryptoleaf receives 20 %. Each company also agrees on a revenue sharing time line for such payouts (e.g., two years, three years etc.) .
